Code_BuildingVariant: identification of the building variant dataset
Code_BuildingSizeClass: code of the building size class
Code_ConstructionYearClass: code of the construction year class
Year1_Building: construction year of the building (or first year of the construction period)
Year2_Building: construction year of the building (or last year of the construction period)
A_C_Ref: energy reference area (conditioned floor area, internal dimensions)
delta_U_ThermalBridging: additional losses of the thermal envelope caused by thermal bridging (supplement to all U-values)
n_air_infiltration: additional air exchange rate, caused by infiltration (surcharge on air exchange rate)

HeatingDays: number of days per year during heating season (average dayly temperature is below or equal the base temperature)
Theta_e: average external air temperature during the heating season
I_Sol_Hor: average global irradiation on horizontal surface during the heating season
I_Sol_East: average global irradiation on vertical surface oriented East during the heating season
I_Sol_South: average global irradiation on vertical surface oriented South during the heating season
I_Sol_West: average global irradiation on vertical surface oriented West during the heating season
I_Sol_North: average global irradiation on vertical surface oriented North during the heating season
Code_BoundaryCond: actually used boundary conditions for energy balance calculation
F_red_htr1: reduction factor, considering the effect of night setback and unheated space, value at h_tr = 1 W/(m_K),
F_red_htr4: reduction factor, considering the effect of night setback and unheated space, value at h_tr = 4 W/(m_K),
n_air_use: average air change rate, due to use of the building
phi_int: average internal heat sources per m_ reference area
g_gl_n: total solar energy transmittance for radiation perpendicular to the glazing
F_sh_hor: reduction factor external shading, horizontal orientation
F_sh_vert: reduction factor external shading, vertical orientations
F_w: reduction factor, considering radiation non-perpendicular to the glazing
c_m: internal heat capacity per m_ reference area
R_Before_Roof_1: thermal resistance of element without insulation, in case that existing insulation is removed during refurbishment
R_Before_Roof_2: thermal resistance of element without insulation, in case that existing insulation is removed during refurbishment
R_Before_Wall_1: thermal resistance of element without insulation, in case that existing insulation is removed during refurbishment
R_Before_Wall_2: thermal resistance of element without insulation, in case that existing insulation is removed during refurbishment
R_Before_Wall_3: thermal resistance of element without insulation, in case that existing insulation is removed during refurbishment
R_Before_Floor_1: thermal resistance of element without insulation, in case that existing insulation is removed during refurbishment
R_Before_Floor_2: thermal resistance of element without insulation, in case that existing insulation is removed during refurbishment
R_Before_Window_1: thermal resistance of element without insulation, in case that existing insulation is removed during refurbishment
R_Before_Window_2: thermal resistance of element without insulation, in case that existing insulation is removed during refurbishment
R_Before_Door_1: thermal resistance of element without insulation, in case that existing insulation is removed during refurbishment
h_Transmission: floor area related heat transfer coefficient by transmission
h_Ventilation: floor area related heat transfer coefficient by ventilation
Sum_DeltaT_for_HeatingDays: accumulated difference between internal and external temperature
F_red_temp: temperature reduction factor, considering the effect of night setback and unheated space
q_ht_tr: floor area related annual transmission losses
q_ht_ve: floor area related annual ventilation losses
Q_Sol_Hor: solar heat load during heating season
Q_Sol_East: solar heat load during heating season
Q_Sol_South: solar heat load during heating season
Q_Sol_West: solar heat load during heating season
Q_Sol_North: solar heat load during heating season
q_sol: floar area related solar heat load during heating season
q_int: floar area related internal heat sources during heating season
a_H: parameter for determination of the gain utilisation factor for heating
gamma_h_gn: heat balance ratio for the heating mode

Number_BuildingVariant: used for different refurbishment variants: 1 = existing state / 2 = standard refurbishment / 3 = ambitious refurbishment
A_C_Ref: mandatory / for transformation from other area types see DATAMINE evaluation
delta_U_ThermalBridging: standard values in W/(m_K):0        minimal0,05   low0,1     medium0,15   high(valid for thermal envelope based on external dimensions)
n_air_infiltration: standard values in 1/h:0,05   minimal0,1     low0,2     medium0,4     high
d_Insulation_Roof_1: relevant in case of replacement by new measure
d_Insulation_Roof_2: relevant in case of replacement by new measure
d_Insulation_Wall_1: relevant in case of replacement by new measure
d_Insulation_Wall_2: relevant in case of replacement by new measure
d_Insulation_Wall_3: relevant in case of replacement by new measure
d_Insulation_Floor_1: relevant in case of replacement by new measure
d_Insulation_Floor_2: relevant in case of replacement by new measure
A_Window_Horizontal: tilted below 30°, otherwise classified as vertical (see below)
F_red_htr1: h_tr = heat transfer coefficient by transmission, devided by A_C,ref; values between h_tr = 1 und h_tr = 4 are interpolated
F_red_htr4: h_tr = heat transfer coefficient by transmission, devided by A_C,ref; values between h_tr = 1 und h_tr = 4 are interpolated
n_air_use: hygienical nessary air exchange rate by opening of windows, by ventilation systems, by parts of infiltration which are usable for necessary air exchange
h_room: the room height is used for the simplified calculation of the air volume
g_gl_n: average for both window types, considering refurbished state
H_Transmission_ThermalBridging: supplemental heat loss due to thermal bridging
h_Transmission: indicator for energy quality of building envelope (compactness + insulation)
F_red_temp: values of F_red_temp are given for h_tr = 1 und h_tr = 4, interpolation of values between
